<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/711983-anyone-else-notice-this-it-seems-to-me">Anyone else notice this? It seems to me Gibson excels at writing unique and rounded female leads, but most his male leads seem like the same &quot;down-on-his-luck average-joe.&quot; 

Case and Bobby Newmark are exceptions, and his male supporting characters are fantastic; but most of his male protagonists--Berry Rydell, Collin Laney, Turner, Slick, Yamazaki, Netherton--all pretty interchangeable.

Thoughts?</a>
</div>
