<div id="review_4397875320" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4397875320" />
    <a title="Judy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3333943-judy"><img alt="Judy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1267037102p2/3333943.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4397875320?book_show_action=true">Dec 22, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Judy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Judy" href="/user/show/3333943-judy">Judy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3333943-judy?shelf=speculative-fiction">speculative-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3333943-judy?shelf=20th-century-fiction">20th-century-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3333943-judy?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3333943-judy?shelf=set-in-california">set-in-california</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4397875320" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2063470904358037174">Some fans of William Gibson did not like this one as much as the books in his Sprawl trilogy. I found it just as good but different. Like his cyberpunk self was growing up a bit. I found the characters more developed. Set in San Francisco and Los Angeles in the early 21st century, Virtual Light is the first of a new trilogy, The Bridge Trilogy. <br/><br/>California is split into two states: No Cal and So Cal. That is not too far from the truth. Since I recently finished PDK&apos;s Dr Bloodmoney, I was happy to</span>
  <span id="freeText2063470904358037174" style="display:none">Some fans of William Gibson did not like this one as much as the books in his Sprawl trilogy. I found it just as good but different. Like his cyberpunk self was growing up a bit. I found the characters more developed. Set in San Francisco and Los Angeles in the early 21st century, Virtual Light is the first of a new trilogy, The Bridge Trilogy. <br /><br />California is split into two states: No Cal and So Cal. That is not too far from the truth. Since I recently finished PDK's Dr Bloodmoney, I was happy to remain in my current home state for a while longer. Surely Dick was an influence on Gibson.<br /><br />Lots of issues about crime from soft and local to hard and global. Somehow he manages to take on just about every issue that was bubbling up in 1983 and expand it into a possible 2005 future. Sure it did not all come true. That is why it is called "speculative fiction," right?<br /><br />When I finished, I just wanted to read the next one right away. In fact, I wanted to read all of his books up to the present, right away. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2063470904358037174" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

